# TBH Companion — required agent docs

Before **implementing** a feature, refactor, or behavior change under `app/`:

1. **Read** (open the file; do not rely on memory) — see `docs/agent/SKILLS.md`:
   - `docs/agent/CODING-GUIDELINES.md` — always
   - `docs/agent/QA.md` — completion gate
2. **Also read when the change touches** paths listed in `docs/agent/SKILLS.md` (layer docs under `docs/agent/layers/`).

**PR review:** `/review-pr <N>` → `.cursor/skills/tbh-reviewer/SKILL.md` (advisory).

Apply during the work, not only at the end. No drive-by refactors outside the task.

**Layer rules:** `AGENTS.md` architecture table + `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.

**Done means:** `docs/agent/QA.md` passed, spike/probe scripts removed when applicable, and required docs were followed — not just green tests.
